cdn.com/11814687-a211-436a-81e1-afb834568fd7/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/2022-03-21_14.28.07_100x.avif" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="100" height="80" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="100" natural-height="80" style="margin-top: auto, margin-bottom: 0"></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1691357709588" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1691357709588"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Grip Strengthener: What Is It, Its Features</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1691357726469" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1691357726469" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>A grip strengthener is a very effective hand exercise tool that’s supposed to improve the strength, dexterity, and endurance of the muscles in your hands and forearms. If you’ve ever seen one of them in person, you probably noticed how compact and portable they are, but these practical little tools pack a punch, and they can offer serious resistance.</p><p>They come in a lot of different forms and usually have adjustable resistance that lets your grip progress gradually. This is particularly beneficial for people who use grip strengtheners for rehabilitation.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1700814491384" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1700814491384" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>At its core, grip training equipment is made to target specific muscle groups in your hands and forearms. They often isolate and exercise individual fingers, which not only improves your grip, but also dexterity. Some of them will allow you to do exercises like pinching, crushing, and extensions — it’s not all about squeezing!</p><p>Another very important feature is their ergonomic design, which makes them fit comfortably in the palm of the hand. It’s a characteristic that’s most obvious when you’ve been using the gripper for a long time because it reduces fatigue.</p><p>You’ll probably first think of athletes when it comes to the people who mostly use hand grippers, and you are right – they’re very popular with athletes, but their uses go way beyond sports, because they can also help people who are dealing with arthritis, carpal tunnel syndrome, or tendon injuries.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1681240893996" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1681240893996" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_module--sm gf_module--xs {{extraClass}}"><!-- Begin Mailchimp Signup Form --><style>.evg-mail-form h3 {margin-top: 0;}.evg-mail-form {margin: 50px 0;border-radius: 7px;border: 1px solid #bbbbbb;padding: 22px;padding-right: 50px;position: relative;font-family: Montserrat,sans-serif;}.evg-mail-form__grid {display: grid;grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr;align-items: center;gap: 50px;}.evg-mail-form__image {max-width: 100%;border-radius: 7px;}.evg-mail-form__inputs {display: grid;gri