t-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Do grip strengtheners really work?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1689974584408" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1689974584408"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">They sure do. They’re very good at improving the strength of your hands as well as dexterity and overall muscle development. They’re beneficial for everyone, but especially for athletes, musicians, and people recovering from hand injuries.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663341660731" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1663341660731"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Do grippers build forearms?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663341660709" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1663341660709"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Yes, and they do so effectively. The repetitive motion of squeezing the hand grip strengthener engages the muscles in your forearm and promotes muscle development.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-al